<subSubSection id="C32E6559E232FFE2FF231977DC7A51D5" pageId="1" pageNumber="577" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B8B36D2E232FFE2FF231977DC7A51D5" blockId="1.[151,1437,1388,1847]" pageId="1" pageNumber="577">
<taxonomicName id="4C344D51E232FFE2FF231977D90852F5" authorityName="Rondani" authorityYear="1850" box="[151,283,1388,1414]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Mimegralla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="577" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B940EAC0E232FFE2FF231977D90852F5" box="[151,283,1388,1414]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="577">Mimegralla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a large, mostly Oriental genus in need of revision and redefinition. All Afrotropical species previously included in the genus are now treated as either 
<taxonomicName id="4C344D51E232FFE2FCB5198BDB7C52D9" box="[769,879,1424,1450]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Hybobata" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="577" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B940EAC0E232FFE2FCB5198BDB7C52D9" box="[769,879,1424,1450]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="577">Hybobata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
or 
<taxonomicName id="4C344D51E232FFE2FC2D198ADD5952D9" authority="Verbeke (Marshall 2017)" authorityName="Verbeke (Marshall" authorityYear="2017" box="[921,1354,1424,1450]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Tanypomyia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="577" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B940EAC0E232FFE2FC2D198ADC3252D9" box="[921,1057,1425,1450]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="577">Tanypomyia</emphasis>
Verbeke (
<bibRefCitation id="EFA54B23E232FFE2FB23198BDD5152D9" author="Marshall, S. A." box="[1175,1346,1424,1450]" pageId="1" pageNumber="577" pagination="244 - 280" refId="ref3171" refString="Marshall, S. A. (2017) Micropezidae (Insecta, Diptera, Acalyptratae) of Madagascar and a revision of the genus Paramimegralla Hennig. Zootaxa, 4290 (2), 244 - 280. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4290.2.2" type="journal article" year="2017">Marshall 2017</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, so the 
<taxonomicName id="4C344D51E232FFE2FF2319AFD90852BD" authorityName="Rondani" authorityYear="1850" box="[151,283,1460,1486]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Mimegralla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="577" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B940EAC0E232FFE2FF2319AFD90852BD" box="[151,283,1460,1486]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="577">Mimegralla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species here newly recorded from the Mascarenes represents the first legitimate record of the genus from the Afrotropical Region. 
<taxonomicName id="4C344D51E232FFE2FE4519C3DAFF5281" baseAuthorityName="Wiedemann" baseAuthorityYear="1830" box="[497,748,1496,1522]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Mimegralla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="577" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="splendens">
<emphasis id="B940EAC0E232FFE2FE4519C3DAFF5281" box="[497,748,1496,1522]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="577">Mimegralla splendens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="130F2A57E232FFE2FD4819C3DB2C5281" box="[764,831,1496,1522]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1960,1985]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,259,1921]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,259,1921]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Paraeurybata taeniata (Macquart), n. comb. A, female ovipositing; B, female; C, wing of male; D, apex of male abdomen, right; E, male; F, head of male. Mimegralla splendens (Wiedemann). G and H, in copula." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3265631/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="577">Figs 1</figureCitation>
G-H) is probably introduced from 
<collectingCountry id="F3237642E232FFE2FB7819C3DD155281" box="[1228,1286,1496,1522]" name="India" pageId="1" pageNumber="577">India</collectingCountry>
or 
<collectingCountry id="F3237642E232FFE2FA9919C3DD8F5281" box="[1325,1436,1496,1522]" name="Sri Lanka" pageId="1" pageNumber="577">Sri Lanka</collectingCountry>
and is now abundant at a few coastal locations in 
<collectingCountry id="F3237642E232FFE2FD7919E7DB2E5165" box="[717,829,1532,1558]" name="Mauritius" pageId="1" pageNumber="577">Mauritius</collectingCountry>
, where larvae probably develop in taro roots. Species identification of 
<taxonomicName id="4C344D51E232FFE2FEE51A3BD9C65149" authorityName="Rondani" authorityYear="1850" box="[337,469,1568,1594]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Mimegralla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="577" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B940EAC0E232FFE2FEE51A3BD9C65149" box="[337,469,1568,1594]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="577">Mimegralla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a problem in the absence of a current revision or even useable descriptions; this species was identified as 
<taxonomicName id="4C344D51E232FFE2FE3E1A5EDAAF512C" authority="(Wiedemann)" authorityName="Wiedemann" baseAuthorityName="Wiedemann" baseAuthorityYear="1830" box="[394,700,1604,1631]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Mimegralla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="577" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="splendens">
<emphasis id="B940EAC0E232FFE2FE3E1A5ED9B2512D" box="[394,417,1605,1630]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="577">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B940EAC0E232FFE2FE1B1A5FDA0E512D" box="[431,541,1604,1630]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="577">splendens</emphasis>
(Wiedemann)
</taxonomicName>
by matching it to the 
<typeStatus id="548F8870E232FFE2FC1A1A5EDBCD512C" box="[942,990,1605,1631]" pageId="1" pageNumber="577">type</typeStatus>
specimen (labelled 
<taxonomicName id="4C344D51E232FFE2FB091A5ED8D951F1" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Mimegralla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="577" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="leucopeza" subSpecies="splendens">
<emphasis id="B940EAC0E232FFE2FB091A5EDCC7512D" box="[1213,1236,1605,1630]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="577">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B940EAC0E232FFE2FB561A5FD8D951F1" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="577">leucopeza splendens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) in the Naturhistorisches Museum in Vienna. 
<taxonomicName id="4C344D51E232FFE2FD7E1A73DBD051F1" baseAuthorityName="Wiedemann" baseAuthorityYear="1830" box="[714,963,1640,1666]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Mimegralla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="577" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="splendens">
<emphasis id="B940EAC0E232FFE2FD7E1A73DBD051F1" box="[714,963,1640,1666]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="577">Mimegralla splendens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which was treated by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFA54B23E232FFE2FB761A73DD8F51F1" author="Steyskal, G. C." box="[1218,1436,1640,1666]" pageId="1" pageNumber="577" pagination="13 - 20" refId="ref3222" refString="Steyskal, G. C. (1977) Family Micropezidae. In: Delfinado, M. D &amp; Hardy, D. E. (Eds.), A catalog of the Diptera of the Oriental Region. Vol. 3. Suborder Cyclorrhapha (excluding division Aschiza). University of Hawaii Press, Honolulu, pp. 13 - 20." type="book chapter" year="1977">Steyskal (1977: 17)</bibRefCitation>
as a subspecies of 
<taxonomicName id="4C344D51E232FFE2FED21A96DA8B51D4" authority="(Wiedemann)" authorityName="Wiedemann" baseAuthorityName="Wiedemann" baseAuthorityYear="1819" box="[358,664,1676,1703]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Mimegralla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="577" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albitarsis">
<emphasis id="B940EAC0E232FFE2FED21A96D96E51D5" box="[358,381,1677,1702]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="577">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B940EAC0E232FFE2FE3F1A97D9E651D5" box="[395,501,1676,1702]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="577">albitarsis</emphasis>
(Wiedemann)
</taxonomicName>
, otherwise occurs in 
<collectingCountry id="F3237642E232FFE2FC301A97DBAD51D5" box="[900,958,1676,1702]" name="India" pageId="1" pageNumber="577">India</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="F3237642E232FFE2FC401A97DC7651D5" box="[1012,1125,1676,1702]" name="Sri Lanka" pageId="1" pageNumber="577">Sri Lanka</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
